<paragraph blockId="61.[189,1398,1964,2025]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
The genus name, a feminine noun, combines ʻ 
<emphasis box="[732,815,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">pseudo</emphasis>
-ʼ (ʻfalseʼ) with 
<taxonomicName box="[1004,1071,1964,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1004,1071,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Cyrta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the name of a superficially similar genus belonging to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dallas" authorityYear="1870" box="[508,703,1999,2025]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Deltocephalinae">Deltocephalinae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[714,855,1999,2025]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Stegelytrini">Stegelytrini</taxonomicName>
